doc.after: By far the largest part of the modern vocabulary of Norwegian dates back to Old Norse The largest source of loanwords is Middle Low German which had a huge influence on Norwegian vocabulary from the late Middle Ages onwards partially even influencing grammatical structures such as genitive constructions At present the main source of new loanwords is English e g rapper e mail catering juice bag originally a loan word to English from Old Norse
